    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Recruitment and Selection Process at L&amp;T Infotech, Bangalore</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Govindareddy Aiswarya</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Recruitment and Selection<br />L&amp;T Infotech,</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5785</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">In L&amp;T Infotech , most of the employees feel that the HR department is good. Among 70 people, 23 people (32.85% of the sample) strongly agree that the recruitment and selection process of the company meets the current requirements. More than half of the sample i.e., 47 people (67.14% of
the sample) strongly agree that the right job is being done by the deserved person in L&amp;T Infotech. Among 70 people, 39 people (55.71% of the sample) are happy with the salary that is offered by the company. 23 people (32.85% of the sample) have been from 0-1yrs with the company, 18 people (25.71% of the sample) have been 1-2 yrs, 18 people (25.71% of the sample) have been 3-4 years, and 11 people (15.71% of the sample) have been more than 4 yrs with the company. 46 people (65.71% of the sample) agree that the employeeâ€™s competency matches with the job specification. 58 people (82.85% of the sample) are satisfied regarding their designation. Both external and internal sources of recruitment are used by 49 people (70% of the sample). 48 members (68.57% of the sample) opted external source of recruitment for the best results. 50 members (71.42% of the sample) consider relevant experience as the most important aspect while short listing a CV. 35 people (50% of the sample) use the existing database as the source of recruitment for the current client. Personal interview is the method of selection adapted by 35 people (50% of the sample). 28 people (40% of the sample) feel that communication skills are neither important nor negligible. 24 people (34.28% of the sample) feel that qualification of the candidate is very important parameter for selecting a candidate. 25 people (35.71%of the sample) feel that confidence is the most important parameter for selecting a candidate. 58 people (82.85% of the sample) feel that technical skills of the candidate are the most important parameter for a candidate to be selected. 55%-70% of the candidates were selected by 24 people (34.28% of the sample). 35 people (50% of the sample) say that the employee turnover rate in the month of March-April is 10%-20%. 25 people (35.71% of the sample) said that the employee requirement on 2012 is 1000-2000. 28 people (40% of the sample) have lined up 100-200 candidates. 60 people (85.72% of the sample) agree that innovative techniques like stress level test, psychometric test) should be added. 63 members (90% of the sample) use both quantitative and qualitative test to gauge the capability and aptitude of the candidates. 24 people (34.28% of the sample) think that supply and demand is important factor.
28 members (40% of the sample) think that image/goodwill is important factor. 25 people (35.71% of the sample) think that economy is neither important nor negligible. 25 people (35.71% of the sample) think that a competitor is an important factor. 27 members (38.57% of the sample) think that unemployment rate is the important factor. 24 people (34.28% of the sample) think that recruitment policy is the important factor. 25 members (35.71% of the sample) think that it is neither important nor negligible. 26 people (37.14% of the sample) think that it is the important factor. 35 people (50% of the sample) think that the cost of recruitment is the most important factor that affects recruitment and selection process. 28 members (40% of the sample) think that it is the important factor.
Most of the employees from the sample i.e., 53 people (75.71% of the sample) are satisfied with the recruitment and selection process in the company.
There is significant relationship between the aspect that is considered while short listing the CV and the method of selection to recruit people.</td></tr>
